modules.description: Provides functions to query CPU features and capabilities, including checking for support of specific instruction sets and processor flags. Works with low-level CPU registers and bitmasks to extract and interpret feature information. Used to enable or disable hardware-specific optimizations at runtime based on detected CPU capabilities.

Provides functions to retrieve and format CPU vendor information, model details, and supported flags. Works with custom types for errors, vendors, flags, and result types encapsulating success or failure. Used to check CPU feature support and determine logical core count for system-specific configuration.
